al-initiatives/brasil/?lang=pt-br"><span class="icl_lang_sel_translated"><span class="icl_lang_sel_bracket"> (</span>Portuguese (Brazil)<span class="icl_lang_sel_bracket">)</span></span></a></li></ul></li></ul></div></div></div> </nav><div id="main-container"><div class="hero-container"><div class="hero-content trans-center"> <picture> <!--[if IE 9]><video style='display: none;'><![endif]--> <source srcset='http://earthinnovation.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/careers-hero_v01.jpg 1920w' media='(min-width: 1441px)'> <source srcset='http://earthinnovation.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/careers-hero_v01-1440x810.jpg 1440w' media='(min-width: 961px)'> <source srcset='http://earthinnovation.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/careers-hero_v01-960x540.jpg 960w' media='(min-width: 481px)'> <source srcset='http://earthinnovation.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/careers-hero_v01-480x270.jpg 480w' > <!--[if IE 9]></video><![endif]--> <img srcset='http://earthinnovation.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/careers-hero_v01-480x270.jpg' alt='Bamboo detail' /> </picture></div><h3 class="page-title absolute-center"><span>Careers</span></h3></div><div id="main-content"><div class="pagenav-container"><div class="pagenav"><h5 class="pagenav-title">Available Positions</h5><ul><li><a href="http://earthinnovation.org/about/careers/#job-5036"> Consultant – Jurisdictional incentives and Payment for Performance mechanisms in Colombia </a></li></ul></div></div><section class="job-container"><div> <article id="job-5036"><div class="overview"><h4 class="job-title">Consultant – Jurisdictional incentives and Payment for Performance mechanisms in Colombia</h4> <small class="metadata"> Posted on April 7, 2016 </small></div><div class="content"><p><strong>BACKGROUND:</strong></p><p>Earth Innovation Institute catalyzes innovative, large-scale transitions to low-emissions rural development in tropical regions through research and policy design that promotes sustainable farming, forestry, and fisheries systems, while improving rural livelihoods and enhancing the capacity of the planet to support life. Through targeted, regional interventions, we seek globally significant increases in farm production, forest cover, fisheries yields, and rural household wellbeing while decreasing emissions of heat-trapping gas.</p><p>We are now working with local partners to design and/or implement transitional strategies for low-emission rural development in Brazil (Mato Grosso, Pará, Acre, national), Indonesia (Central Kalimantan, West Papua), Colombia (national), Peru (the Peruvian Amazon), and Mexico (Chiapas State).</p><p><strong>SUMMARY:</strong></p><p>Reporting directly to the National Program Coordinator of Colombia, the Financial Expert will coordinate and support research, provide technical advice, writing and editing of reports and manuscripts and proposal development. Research will focus on jurisdictional incentives and payment for performance mechanisms, analysis of existing financial mechanisms and opportunities to promote payment for performance mechanisms. The candidate will play a key role in the facilitation of processes and the provision of technical advice to government agencies, private sector and civil society partners in Colombia.</p><p><strong>ACTIVITIES AND DELIVERABLES:</strong></p><p><strong>(A) Jurisdictional incentives and Payment for Performance mechanisms </strong></p><p>The objective of this work is to engage with key stakeholders to build a proposal for the implementation of jurisdictional incentives to be implemented under the umbrella of the Amazon Vision Program in Colombia and analyze other mechanisms that could complement payment for performance mechanisms (e.g. taxes, supply chains initiatives, etc.).</p><p>Activities will include:</p><ul><li>Revise existing proposals of financial mechanisms and define a road map for implementation in coordination with Ministry of Agriculture, FINAGRO and other relevant organizations (donor governments, multilateral institutions, local) the to</li><li>Support to the Ministry of Agriculture and FINAGRO in the development of analysis needed for the design and implementation of financial mechanisms included in the Amazon Vision Program.</li><li>Development of draft documents to promote technical discussions with relevant actors.</li><li>Identification of other jurisdictional incentives that could complement the implementation of financial mechanisms in Caquetá and Guaviare.</li></ul><p><strong>(B) Productive alliances and payment for performance and sustainability along supply chains </strong></p><p>Productive Alliances Program of MADR is one of the mechanisms identified as useful to promote reduction of deforestation in the Amazon. Amazon Vision program is planning to build from existing work of this program and develop a specific mechanism to promote private sector engagement in the amazon to support sustainable businesses.</p><p>Activities will include:</p><ol><li>Based on existing analysis and proposal, facilitate meetings to discuss the progress of the Productive Alliances Program and agree upon the adjustments needed to implement the program in the Amazon</li><li>Support financial and cost analysis for the implementation of the program in Caquetá and Guaviare</li></ol><p><strong> </strong><strong>(C) Policy paper on financial mechanisms to promote jurisdictional sustainability in the Amazon </strong></p><p>Based on the proposal of financial mechanisms developed for the Amazon Vision Program of Colombia, EII will present a policy brief on existing financial mechanisms in Colombia and recommendations for the implementation of financial incentives that could support zero-net deforestation goals in the Amazon</p><p>Activities will include</p><ol><li>Revision of existing information about financial incentives in Colombia (studies previously developed by Forest Trends, EII and partners)</li><li>Lead the writing of a policy brief on potential mechanisms that could support national LED-R strategies in Colombia and jurisdictional sustainability in the Amazon.</li></ol><p><strong>(D) Support EII work on territorial approach </strong></p><p>EII is promoting activities in Caquetá, initially supporting supply chains that could drive transformation into LED-R at jurisdictional level. Success of supply chains interventions will depend on the existence of positive incentives targeted to local smallholders and indigenous communities.</p><p>Activities will include:</p><ol><li>Technical support to the EII team in the analysis of incentives applicable at jurisdictional level</li><li>Provide ad hoc reviews of and input into EII communications materials (presentations, papers, etc.); and</li><li>Participate meetings and events</li></ol><p><strong>REQUIRED QUALIFICATIONS AND EXPERIENCE:</strong></p><ul><li>Master degree or equivalent in economy plus 3 to 5 years of experience on incentives.</li><li>Minimum three to five years of work experience in financial incentives and non-financial instruments</li><li>Practical experience in structuring financial mechanisms (credit via commercial banks, agricultural lending, administering government incentive programs, public-private partnerships)</li><li>Experience with rural development financial mechanisms in Colombia</li><li>Knowledge of and proven ability to perform quantitative analysis</li><li>Spanish and English fluency</li></ul><p><strong>APPLICATION DEADLINE: April 15, 2016</strong></p><p><strong> </strong><strong>CONTRACT TERM: Eight (8) months</strong></p><p><strong> </strong><strong>DESIRED START DATE: ASAP</strong></p><p><strong>APPLICATION INSTRUCTIONS:</strong><strong> </strong>Please send expression of interest and CV/summary of qualifications, and proposed compensation to Maria Teresa Becerra &#8211; mtbecerra@earthinnovation.org.</p><p><a name="_edn1"></a></p></div> </article></div> </section><div class="footnotes"><h5 class="title">Organizational Summary:</h5><p>The Earth Innovation Institute is a not-for-profit, independent research institute with headquarters in San Francisco and offices in Brazil, Indonesia and Colombia. We pursue our goals of slowing climate change, conserving tropical forests and fisheries, and improving rural livelihoods by promoting sustainable rural development through a blend of research, consensus-building, policy analysis and reform, and private sector engagement.</p><p><strong>Earth Innovation Institute is an equal opportunity employer. All candidates receive consideration for employment without regard to race, color, religion, sex, or national origin.</strong></p></div></div></div><div id="footer"><div id="footer-widgets" class="group section textured"><div class="footer-widget social-links"><div class="section"><div class="list-container col span_1_of_2"><ul><li><h6 class="widget-title">Follow Us</h6></li><li> <a class="facebook-small social-icon" target="_blank" href="https://www.facebook.com/Earth.Innovation"></a> <a href="https://www.facebook.com/Earth.Innovation" target="_blank">Facebook</a></li><li> <a class="linkedin-small social-icon" target="_blank" href="https://www.linkedin.com/company/earth-innovation-institute?trk=biz-companies-cym"></a> <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/company/earth-innovation-institute?trk=biz-companies-cym" target="_blank">LinkedIn</a></li><li> <a class="twitter-small social-icon" target="_blank" href="https://twitter.com/EarthInnovate"></a> <a href="https://twitter.com/EarthInnovate" target="_blank">Twitter</a></li></ul></div><div class="newsletter col span_1_of_2"> <a target="_blank" href="https://app.etapestry.com/onlineforms/EarthInnovationInstitute/signup-1.html" alt="Sign up for the Earth Innovation Institute Newsletter"> <button class="blue newsletter-title">Stay Connected</button> </a></div></div></div><div class="addresses"><div class="section"><div class="col span_1_of_2 mailing"> <address class="vcard"> <span class="adr"><strong>Mailing Address:</strong></span> <span class="street-address">